# Flatpak refs to actively uninstall on deployed systems. Read by
# sideral-flatpak-install.service on every boot.
#
# Use when a ref is dropped from /etc/flatpak-manifest AND we want
# existing user installations of that ref to be removed — not just
# skipped on future fresh installs. Removing a line from the manifest
# alone won't uninstall the ref from systems whose /var/lib/flatpak was
# seeded at an older image rebase; this file is the active-removal
# escape hatch.
#
# Format: bare ref per line. Lines starting with # and blank lines are
# ignored. Idempotent — `flatpak uninstall` on a ref that's not
# installed is skipped via a `flatpak info` precheck, so this file can
# grow over time without measurable boot-time impact.
#
# Drop entries when enough release cycles have passed that any system
# still on the old manifest would have purged the ref already. Two or
# three image rebases is usually plenty.

# Removed 2026-05-02 (sideral-flatpaks 0.0.0-5). Flatseal covers
# permissions; Warehouse's bulk-uninstall / snapshot UX duplicates
# `flatpak uninstall` + ostree rollback without adding enough on top.
